THE
ORBIT
OF
A
CHARGED
PARTICLE
IN
A
CONSTANT
MAGNETIC
FIELD
AND
A
SINUSOIDAL
ELECTRIC
FIELD
EXPLICIT
EXPRESSIONS
ARE
OBTAINED
FOR
THE
PARTICLE
ORBIT
ASSUMING
THAT
THE
EFFECT
OF
THE
ELECTRIC
FIELD
ON
THE
PARTICLE
IS
MERELY
TO
PRODUCE
A
PERTURBATION
ON
THE
MOTION
WHICH
IT
WOULD
DESCRIBE
IN
THE
ABSENCE
OF
TH
FIELD
